    "Even linear perturbation theory predicts an amplitude growth[48- 51], but such growth is dependent on the initial data, and not easy to disentangle from other nonlinear effects in a binary merger.",
    "Lacking a detailed understanding of this process, amplitudes are often assumed to be constant at late enough times.",
    "Note that the orbital angular momentum direction coincides with the angular momentum of the final BH for non-precessing binaries."
